# MedBook – Appointments Web App (Assignment 4)

This project is a Node.js + Express + MongoDB web application with a production-style UI.

Students:
Aida Kentay 
Tomiris Kassymova

Group: SE-2428

## Features
- Full CRUD for Appointments via Web UI
- Sessions-based authentication (express-session)
- Session stored in MongoDB (connect-mongo)
- Protected write operations (POST / PUT / DELETE)
- Password hashing with bcrypt
- Secure cookies (HttpOnly, Secure in production)
- Validation + safe error handling

## Tech Stack
- Node.js
- Express.js
- MongoDB + Mongoose
- express-session + connect-mongo
- bcrypt
- HTML/CSS/JS (Vanilla)

## Domain Entity
Appointments contain:
- patientName
- doctorName
- date
- time
- department
- reason
- status (scheduled / completed / cancelled)
- phone

## Demo Requirements (Defense)
- Open the deployed URL
- Show CRUD via UI
- Show login + sessions
- Show that unauthorized users cannot create/update/delete

